{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Adrian Kohler: Well, we're here today"},{"time":2000,"text":"to talk about the evolution of a puppet horse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6000,"text":"Basil Jones: But actually we're going to start this evolution"},{"time":9000,"text":"with a hyena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11000,"text":"AK: The ancestor of the horse."},{"time":13000,"text":"Okay, we'll do something with it."},{"time":46000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":50000,"text":"Hahahaha."},{"time":69000,"text":"The hyena is the ancestor of the horse"},{"time":72000,"text":"because it was part of a production"},{"time":74000,"text":"called \"Faustus in Africa,\""},{"time":76000,"text":"a Handspring Production from 1995,"},{"time":79000,"text":"where it had to play draughts with Helen of Troy."},{"time":82000,"text":"This production was directed"},{"time":84000,"text":"by South African artist and theater director,"},{"time":86000,"text":"William Kentridge."},{"time":88000,"text":"So it needed a very articulate front paw."},{"time":96000,"text":"But, like all puppets, it has other attributes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"BJ: One of them is breath,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and it kind of breathes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"AK: Haa haa haaa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"BJ: Breath is really important for us."},{"time":112000,"text":"It's the kind of original movement"},{"time":114000,"text":"for any puppet for us onstage."},{"time":117000,"text":"It's the thing that distinguishes the puppet --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"AK: Oops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"BJ: From an actor."},{"time":124000,"text":"Puppets always have to try to be alive."},{"time":127000,"text":"It's their kind of ur-story onstage,"},{"time":131000,"text":"that desperation to live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"AK: Yeah, it's basically a dead object, as you can see,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and it only lives"},{"time":138000,"text":"because you make it."},{"time":140000,"text":"An actor struggles to die onstage,"},{"time":142000,"text":"but a puppet has to struggle to live."},{"time":144000,"text":"And in a way that's a metaphor for life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"BJ: So every moment it's on the stage, it's making the struggle."},{"time":149000,"text":"So we call this"},{"time":152000,"text":"a piece of emotional engineering"},{"time":156000,"text":"that uses up-to-the-minute"},{"time":159000,"text":"17th century technology --"},{"time":161000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":163000,"text":"to turn nouns"},{"time":165000,"text":"into verbs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"AK: Well actually I prefer to say"},{"time":169000,"text":"that it's an object"},{"time":171000,"text":"constructed out of wood and cloth"},{"time":173000,"text":"with movement built into it"},{"time":175000,"text":"to persuade you to believe that it has life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"BJ: Okay so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180000,"text":"AK: It has ears that move passively"},{"time":182000,"text":"when the head goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"BJ: And it has these bulkheads"},{"time":187000,"text":"made out of plywood,"},{"time":189000,"text":"covered with fabric --"},{"time":191000,"text":"curiously similar, in fact,"},{"time":193000,"text":"to the plywood canoes"},{"time":195000,"text":"that Adrian's father used to make"},{"time":197000,"text":"when he was a boy in their workshop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"AK: In Port Elizabeth, the village outside Port Elizabeth in South Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"BJ: His mother was a puppeteer."},{"time":205000,"text":"And when we met at art school"},{"time":207000,"text":"and fell in love"},{"time":209000,"text":"in 1971,"},{"time":211000,"text":"I hated puppets."},{"time":213000,"text":"I really thought they were so beneath me."},{"time":216000,"text":"I wanted to become an avant-garde artist --"},{"time":219000,"text":"and Punch and Judy was certainly not where I wanted to go."},{"time":222000,"text":"And, in fact, it took about 10 years"}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"to discover"},{"time":226000,"text":"the Bambara Bamana puppets of Mali in West Africa,"},{"time":230000,"text":"where there's a fabulous tradition of puppetry,"},{"time":234000,"text":"to learn a renewed, or a new, respect"},{"time":238000,"text":"for this art form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"AK: So in 1981, I persuaded Basil and some friends of mine"},{"time":243000,"text":"to form a puppet company."},{"time":245000,"text":"And 20 years later, miraculously,"},{"time":248000,"text":"we collaborated with a company from Mali,"},{"time":250000,"text":"the Sogolon Marionette Troupe of Bamako,"},{"time":253000,"text":"where we made a piece about a tall giraffe."},{"time":255000,"text":"It was just called \"Tall Horse,\" which was a life-sized giraffe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"BJ: And here again, you see the same structure."},{"time":260000,"text":"The bulkheads have now turned into hoops of cane,"},{"time":265000,"text":"but it's ultimately the same structure."},{"time":267000,"text":"It's got two people inside it on stilts,"},{"time":269000,"text":"which give them the height,"},{"time":271000,"text":"and somebody in the front"},{"time":273000,"text":"who's using a kind of steering wheel to move that head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"AK: The person in the hind legs"},{"time":278000,"text":"is also controlling the tail, a bit like the hyena --"},{"time":281000,"text":"same mechanism, just a bit bigger."},{"time":284000,"text":"And he's controlling the ear movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"BJ: So this production"},{"time":290000,"text":"was seen by Tom Morris"},{"time":292000,"text":"of the National Theatre in London."},{"time":294000,"text":"And just around that time,"},{"time":297000,"text":"his mother had said,"},{"time":299000,"text":"\"Have you seen this book by Michael Morpurgo"},{"time":302000,"text":"called 'War Horse'?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":304000,"text":"AK: It's about a boy who falls in love with a horse."},{"time":306000,"text":"The horse is sold to the First World War,"},{"time":308000,"text":"and he joins up to find his horse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"BJ: So Tom gave us a call and said,"},{"time":312000,"text":"\"Do you think you could make us a horse"},{"time":315000,"text":"for a show to happen at the National Theatre?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"AK: It seemed a lovely idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"BJ: But it had to ride. It had to have a rider."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"AK: It had to have a rider,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and it had to participate in cavalry charges."},{"time":326000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":329000,"text":"A play about early 20th century plowing technology"},{"time":331000,"text":"and cavalry charges"},{"time":333000,"text":"was a little bit of a challenge for the accounting department"},{"time":335000,"text":"at the National Theatre in London."},{"time":337000,"text":"But they agreed to go along with it for a while."},{"time":339000,"text":"So we began with a test."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"BJ: This is Adrian and Thys Stander,"},{"time":344000,"text":"who went on to actually design the cane system for the horse,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and our next-door neighbor Katherine,"},{"time":350000,"text":"riding on a ladder."},{"time":352000,"text":"The weight is really difficult when it's up above your head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355000,"text":"AK: And once we put Katherine"},{"time":357000,"text":"through that particular brand of hell,"},{"time":359000,"text":"we knew that we might be able to make a horse, which could be ridden."},{"time":362000,"text":"So we made a model."},{"time":364000,"text":"This is a cardboard model,"},{"time":366000,"text":"a little bit smaller than the hyena."},{"time":368000,"text":"You'll notice that the legs are plywood legs"},{"time":370000,"text":"and the canoe structure is still there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"BJ: And the two manipulators are inside."},{"time":374000,"text":"But we didn't realize at the time"},{"time":376000,"text":"that we actually needed a third manipulator,"},{"time":379000,"text":"because we couldn't manipulate the neck"},{"time":381000,"text":"from inside"},{"time":383000,"text":"and walk the horse at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"AK: We started work on the prototype"},{"time":388000,"text":"after the model was approved,"},{"time":390000,"text":"and the prototype took a bit longer"},{"time":392000,"text":"than we anticipated."},{"time":394000,"text":"We had to throw out the plywood legs and make new cane ones."},{"time":397000,"text":"And we had a crate built for it."},{"time":399000,"text":"It had to be shipped to London."},{"time":401000,"text":"We were going to test-drive it on the street outside of our house in Cape Town,"},{"time":404000,"text":"and it got to midnight and we hadn't done that yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"BJ: So we got a camera,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and we posed the puppet"},{"time":412000,"text":"in various galloping stances."},{"time":417000,"text":"And we sent it off"},{"time":420000,"text":"to the National Theatre,"},{"time":422000,"text":"hoping that they believed"},{"time":424000,"text":"that we created something that worked."},{"time":426000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":428000,"text":"AK: A month later, we were there in London"},{"time":430000,"text":"with this big box and a studio full of people about to work with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"BJ: About 40 people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436000,"text":"AK: We were terrified."},{"time":438000,"text":"We opened the lid, we took the horse out,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and it did work; it walked and it was able to be ridden."},{"time":443000,"text":"Here I have an 18-second clip"},{"time":445000,"text":"of the very first walk of the prototype."},{"time":448000,"text":"This is in the National Theatre studio,"},{"time":450000,"text":"the place where they cook new ideas."},{"time":452000,"text":"It had by no means got the green light yet."},{"time":462000,"text":"The choreographer, Toby Sedgwick,"},{"time":464000,"text":"invented a beautiful sequence"},{"time":466000,"text":"where the baby horse,"},{"time":468000,"text":"which was made out of sticks and bits of twigs,"},{"time":471000,"text":"grew up into the big horse."},{"time":473000,"text":"And Nick Starr, the director of the National Theatre,"},{"time":476000,"text":"saw that particular moment, he was standing next to me -- he nearly wet himself."},{"time":479000,"text":"And so the show was given the green light."},{"time":482000,"text":"And we went back to Cape Town and redesigned the horse completely."},{"time":485000,"text":"Here is the plan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"And here is our factory in Cape Town"},{"time":493000,"text":"where we make horses."},{"time":496000,"text":"You can see quite a lot of skeletons in the background there."},{"time":500000,"text":"The horses are completely handmade."},{"time":503000,"text":"There is very little 20th century technology in them."},{"time":506000,"text":"We used a bit of laser cutting on the plywood"},{"time":508000,"text":"and some of the aluminum pieces."},{"time":510000,"text":"But because they have to be light and flexible,"},{"time":512000,"text":"and each one of them is different,"},{"time":515000,"text":"they can't be mass-produced, unfortunately."},{"time":518000,"text":"So here are some half-finished horses"},{"time":521000,"text":"ready to be worked in London."},{"time":524000,"text":"And now we would like to introduce you"},{"time":526000,"text":"to Joey."},{"time":529000,"text":"Joey boy, you there?"},{"time":532000,"text":"Joey."},{"time":535000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":553000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":576000,"text":"Joey."},{"time":578000,"text":"Joey, come here."},{"time":595000,"text":"No, no, I haven't got it."},{"time":597000,"text":"He's got it; it's in his pocket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"BJ: Joey."},{"time":613000,"text":"AK: Joey, Joey, Joey, Joey."},{"time":618000,"text":"Come here. Stand here where people can see you."},{"time":628000,"text":"Move around. Come on."},{"time":633000,"text":"I'd just like to describe --"},{"time":635000,"text":"I won't talk too loud. He might get irritated."},{"time":640000,"text":"Here, Craig is working the head."},{"time":643000,"text":"He has bicycle brake cables"},{"time":645000,"text":"going down to the head control in his hand."},{"time":648000,"text":"Each one of them"},{"time":650000,"text":"operates either an ear, separately,"},{"time":653000,"text":"or the head, up and down."},{"time":655000,"text":"But he also controls the head directly"},{"time":658000,"text":"by using his hand."},{"time":660000,"text":"The ears are obviously"},{"time":662000,"text":"a very important emotional indicator of the horse."},{"time":665000,"text":"When they point right back,"},{"time":669000,"text":"the horse is fearful or angry,"},{"time":673000,"text":"depending upon what's going on in front of him, around him."},{"time":676000,"text":"Or, when he's more relaxed, the head comes down"},{"time":678000,"text":"and the ears listen, either side."},{"time":683000,"text":"Horses' hearing is very important."},{"time":685000,"text":"It's almost more important than their eyesight."},{"time":689000,"text":"Over here,"},{"time":691000,"text":"Tommy's got what you call the heart position."},{"time":694000,"text":"He's working the leg."},{"time":696000,"text":"You see the string tendon from the hyena,"},{"time":699000,"text":"the hyena's front leg,"},{"time":702000,"text":"automatically pulls the hoop up."},{"time":705000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":710000,"text":"Horses are so unpredictable."},{"time":712000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":716000,"text":"The way a hoof comes up with a horse"},{"time":719000,"text":"immediately gives you the feeling"},{"time":721000,"text":"that it's a convincing horse action."},{"time":723000,"text":"The hind legs have got the same action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729000,"text":"BJ: And Mikey also has,"},{"time":731000,"text":"in his fingers,"},{"time":733000,"text":"the ability to move the tail"},{"time":735000,"text":"from left to right,"},{"time":737000,"text":"and up and down with the other hand."},{"time":739000,"text":"And together, there's quite a complex possibility"},{"time":742000,"text":"of tail expression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"AK: You want to say something about the breathing?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"BJ: We had a big challenge with breathing."},{"time":749000,"text":"Adrian thought"},{"time":751000,"text":"that he was going to have to split the chest of the puppet in two"},{"time":753000,"text":"and make it breathe like that --"},{"time":755000,"text":"because that's how a horse would breathe, with an expanded chest."},{"time":758000,"text":"But we realized"},{"time":760000,"text":"that, if that were to be happening,"},{"time":762000,"text":"you wouldn't, as an audience, see the breath."},{"time":764000,"text":"So he made a channel in here,"},{"time":768000,"text":"and the chest moves up and down in that channel."},{"time":771000,"text":"So it's anti-naturalistic really, the up and down movement,"},{"time":773000,"text":"but it feels like breath."},{"time":775000,"text":"And it's very, very simple"},{"time":777000,"text":"because all that happens"},{"time":779000,"text":"is that the puppeteer breathes with his knees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"AK: Other emotional stuff."},{"time":787000,"text":"If I were to touch the horse here"},{"time":789000,"text":"on his skin,"},{"time":792000,"text":"the heart puppeteer can shake the body from inside"},{"time":795000,"text":"and get the skin to quiver."},{"time":797000,"text":"You'll notice, of course,"},{"time":799000,"text":"that the puppet is made out of cane lines."},{"time":801000,"text":"And I would like you to believe that it was an aesthetic choice,"},{"time":804000,"text":"that I was making a three-dimensional drawing of a horse"},{"time":806000,"text":"that somehow moves in space."},{"time":808000,"text":"But of course, it was the cane is light,"},{"time":810000,"text":"the cane is flexible, the cane is durable"},{"time":812000,"text":"and the cane is moldable."},{"time":814000,"text":"And so it was a very practical reason why it was made of cane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"The skin itself"},{"time":819000,"text":"is made out of a see-through nylon mesh,"},{"time":821000,"text":"which, if the lighting designer"},{"time":823000,"text":"wants the horse to almost disappear,"},{"time":825000,"text":"she can light the background"},{"time":827000,"text":"and the horse becomes ghostlike."},{"time":830000,"text":"You see the skeletal structure of it."},{"time":832000,"text":"Or if you light it from above, it becomes more solid."},{"time":835000,"text":"Again, that was a practical consideration."},{"time":838000,"text":"The guys inside the horse have to be able to see out."},{"time":841000,"text":"They have to be able to act"},{"time":843000,"text":"along with their fellow actors in the production."},{"time":846000,"text":"And it's very much an in-the-moment activity that they're engaged in."},{"time":849000,"text":"It's three heads making one character."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852000,"text":"But now we would like you to put Joey through some paces."},{"time":893000,"text":"And plant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"(Whinny)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":910000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":912000,"text":"And now just --"},{"time":914000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":922000,"text":"All the way from sunny California"},{"time":924000,"text":"we have Zem Joaquin"},{"time":926000,"text":"who's going to ride the horse for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":983000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":993000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1014000,"text":"So we would like to stress"},{"time":1016000,"text":"that the performance you see in the horse"},{"time":1018000,"text":"is three guys"},{"time":1020000,"text":"who have studied horse behavior incredibly thoroughly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023000,"text":"BJ: Not being able to talk to one another"},{"time":1025000,"text":"while they're onstage"},{"time":1027000,"text":"because they're mic'd."},{"time":1029000,"text":"The sound that that very large chest makes, of the horse --"},{"time":1032000,"text":"the whinnying and the nickering and everything --"},{"time":1035000,"text":"that starts usually with one performer,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"carries on with a second person"},{"time":1040000,"text":"and ends with a third."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042000,"text":"AK: Mikey Brett from Leicestershire."},{"time":1045000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1052000,"text":"Mikey Brett, Craig, Leo,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"Zem Joaquin and Basil and me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1058000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1061000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}